channel.title: Compile error
channel.description:
[code]client.java:14746: not a statement Case 75: ^ client.java:14746: ';' expected Case 75: ^ client.java:14756: orphaned case case 39: ^ client.java:15069: orphaned case case 131: ^ 4 errors Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
Any help?

item.title: Compile error
item.dc:creator: @deathschaos9 DeathsChaos9
item.description:
@deathschaos9 wrote:

[quote=“The Reaper X, post:9, topic:335986”][quote author=deathschaos9 link=topic=432365.msg3174257#msg3174257 date=1270684198]
Case has to be lowercase, case 39 and 131 exist outside of a switch statement.
[/quote]An orphaned case could also mean that you’ve stated the case twice in the switch statement.[/quote]

That would throw duplicate case label.

Read full topic

item.dc:creator: @deathschaos9 DeathsChaos9
item.description:
@deathschaos9 wrote:

It makes perfect sense… Case needs to be lowercase… as in case not Case… Java is case sensitive if you haven’t noticed…
Telling someone to delete what gave them an error is pointless. Of course it gets rid of the error! They post for help so that they don’t have to delete what they added.

item.description:

If you have added anything delete it and re-compile.

Sometimes if you add something wrong it throws other stuff off.

Also BTW if you get the 100 errors delete what you just added and some times it fixes it.
